00:24:24.320 --> 00:24:28.320
 The following function is a shell sort for sorting an array of integers.

00:24:28.320 --> 00:24:33.000
 The basic idea of the shell sort is that in early stages,

00:24:33.000 --> 00:24:37.920
 far apart elements are compared rather than adjacent ones, as in simple interchange sorts.

00:24:37.920 --> 00:24:41.080
 This tends to eliminate large amounts of disorder quickly, so

00:24:41.080 --> 00:24:43.400
 later stages have less work to do.

00:24:43.400 --> 00:24:47.240
 The interval between the compared elements is gradually decreased to one,

00:24:47.240 --> 00:24:51.640
 at which point the sort becomes an effectively adjacent interchange method.

00:24:51.640 --> 00:24:57.200
