00:28:37.960 --> 00:28:42.200
 Section 3.6, loops, do while.

00:28:43.720 --> 00:28:48.160
 The while and for loops share the desirable attribute of testing the termination condition

00:28:48.160 --> 00:28:52.160
 at the top rather than at the bottom, as we discussed in chapter one.

00:28:52.160 --> 00:28:53.960
 The third loop in C, the do while,

00:28:53.960 --> 00:28:57.840
 tests at the bottom after making each pass through the loop body.

00:28:57.840 --> 00:29:01.520
 The body is always executed at least once.

00:29:01.520 --> 00:29:03.720
 The syntax is as follows.

00:29:03.720 --> 00:29:08.800
 Do, statement, while, open parenthesis, expression, close parenthesis, semicolon.

00:29:08.800 --> 00:29:12.880
 The statement is executed, then the expression is evaluated.

00:29:12.880 --> 00:29:16.480
 If it is true, statement is evaluated again, and so on.

00:29:16.480 --> 00:29:19.240
 If the expression becomes false, the loop terminates.

00:29:19.240 --> 00:29:24.960
 As might be expected, do while is much less used than while and for,

00:29:24.960 --> 00:29:27.040
 accounting perhaps 5% of all loops.

00:29:27.040 --> 00:29:33.600
 Nonetheless, it is from time to time valuable as in the following function i to a,

00:29:33.600 --> 00:29:37.800
