00:32:45.080 --> 00:32:50.840
 The break statement provides an early exit from a for, while, or

00:32:50.840 --> 00:32:53.960
 do, just as it does from the switch statement.

00:32:53.960 --> 00:32:56.920
 A break statement causes the innermost enclosing loop or

00:32:56.920 --> 00:32:59.720
 switch to be exited immediately.

00:32:59.720 --> 00:33:02.920
