00:42:10.680 --> 00:42:18.400
 Section 3.9, go to's and labels.

00:42:18.400 --> 00:42:25.920
 C provides the infinitely abusable go to statement and labels to branch to.

00:42:25.920 --> 00:42:29.240
 Formally, the go to is never necessary.

00:42:29.240 --> 00:42:33.840
 And in practice, it is almost always easy to write code without it.

00:42:33.840 --> 00:42:36.640
 We have not used go to in this book.

00:42:36.640 --> 00:42:41.480
 Nevertheless, we will suggest a few situations where go to's might find a place.

00:42:41.480 --> 00:42:46.520
 The most common use is to abandon processing in some deeply nested structure,

00:42:46.520 --> 00:42:49.360
 such as breaking out of two loops at once.

00:42:49.360 --> 00:42:52.880
 The break statement cannot be used directly since it leaves the only,

00:42:52.880 --> 00:42:56.480
 the most innermost loop thus.

00:42:56.480 --> 00:42:59.440
 For, open parenthesis, dot, dot, dot, close parenthesis.

00:42:59.440 --> 00:43:02.920
